    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that socioeconomics is a big part of it, but i'm looking for the actual statistical trends that show the disparities. like, even when you control for income, there's still certain groups that show way higher rates in the official reports. if im writing a paper, i need to address the raw data trends first before i pivot to the systemic causes. can u just summarize what the standard datasets actually show regarding the distribution of arrests across different racial groups?",
